    {
      "id": "c32d53867c704f1ff6d1baac2e8d35b7a094d77b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 11:23:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt would be great if you could also get the other HPE developers to update their info in the file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "343dd7adf16645906a8f3ec23dccc606a9877949",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 130,
        "name": "Nikitas Angelinas",
        "email": "nikitas.angelinas@hpe.com",
        "username": "nikitas_angelinas"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 17:52:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSergey, should we also add HPE entries in the .mailmap file in this patchset?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4ea6d79240b3172993d9231d583afb6927b0611f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 378,
        "name": "Sergey Cheremencev",
        "email": "scherementsev@ddn.com",
        "username": "scheremencev"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 18:58:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Sergey, should we also add HPE entries in the .mailmap file in this\n > patchset?\n\nHonestly, I didn't know about this file :). Yes, I think we can do this here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6a01f36433e498bb5ffeca7fc3ccb92e240d0aef",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 378,
        "name": "Sergey Cheremencev",
        "email": "scherementsev@ddn.com",
        "username": "scheremencev"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 19:01:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It would be great if you could also get the other HPE developers to\n > update their info in the file.\n\nI am working on that. Let's wait a week. I will update the patch with all hpe developers who is agree to be added.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c188320a928d5b7580bc6e4c3a5901dbf0e1a3d6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-13 20:05:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNote the .mailmap entries need to be in logical order, so the mapping to HPE should be at the end, before the \"other\" entries.  That allows mapping a series of emails properly (eg. @xyratex, @seagate, @cray, @hpe).\n\nI would also ask that everyone at HPE update the email addresses in their accounts in Gerrit rather than creating new accounts. There are already too many duplicates due various people, I don't really want to see more.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ecafb1a043c2c096d2dfc6bd3809b1ff57be34a3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-27 16:44:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
